overview: The user initiated a request for a comprehensive aesthetic review and
  improvement of their sleep questionnaire application, feeling its current
  design was too generic. The agent began by thoroughly reviewing the existing
  styling, identifying areas such as the color palette, typography, spacing,
  form elements, and overall visual interest. A new sleep-themed color palette
  was introduced, along with custom utility classes for gradients and shadows.
  The main questionnaire form layout was redesigned with decorative background
  elements and an improved progress indicator. The welcome screen (IntroSection)
  was enhanced with a hero section and feature cards. All core UI components
  like checkboxes, radio buttons, sliders, and cards received significant
  styling updates for a more modern and cohesive look. The agent then
  systematically applied these new styling conventions across all questionnaire
  sections, replacing old gray-bordered boxes with themed card-style groupings.
  During the process, a console error related to  values in input fields
  was identified and fixed by modifying the  component to safely handle
  such values. Finally, after user feedback on remaining inconsistencies in the
  Report section's hardcoded colors, these were also updated to align with the
  new sleep theme, along with alert colors and section border opacities,
  resulting in a visually appealing and consistent application.
